{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Hosted Lean proof: jayyhk proof of 990 (state complete) https://github.com/Jayyhk/erdos-lean/blob/main/problems/990/Erdos990.lean.","id":"vf_2acba1b0c50f136a","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Hosted Lean proof: plby proof of 990 (state complete) https://github.com/plby/lean-proofs/blob/main/src/v4.29.1/ErdosProblems/Erdos990.lean.","id":"vf_322f7c6724cea5bc","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Full solution.","id":"vf_addc4947994fe93e","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #990: declared status 'disproved'. Formalized: no. Let $f=a_0+\\cdots+a_dx^d\\in \\mathbb{C}[x]$ be a polynomial. Is it true that, if $f$ has roots $z_1,\\ldots,z_d$ with corresponding arguments $\\theta_1,\\ldots,\\theta_d\\in [0,2\\pi]$, then for all intervals $I\\subseteq [0,2\\pi]$\\[\\left\\lvert (\\# \\theta_i \\in I) - \\frac{\\lvert I\\rvert}{2\\pi}d\\right\\rvert \\ll \\left(n\\log M\\right)^{1/2},\\]where $n$ is the number of non-zero coefficients of $f$ and\\[M=\\frac{\\lvert a_0\\rvert+\\cdots +\\lvert a_d\\rvert}{(\\lvert a_0\\rvert\\lvert a_d\\rvert)^{1/2}}.\\] Current best: Erd\\H{o}s and Tur\\'{a}n \\cite{ErTu50} proved such an upper bound with $n$ replaced by $d$. Prize: no. Tags: analysis.","id":"vf_d3e3d3800f4dc92f","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"claim":"Pinned Formal Conjectures activity classification; integration activity does not establish mathematical truth.","id":"activity:fc-proof_link_edit:990","kind":"proof_link_edit","lifecycle":"banked","source_ref":"sources/formal-conjectures-activity.yaml#problem-990","trust":"declared"}],"activity_types":["proof_link_edit"],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[{"commit":"8f6648ff0fbd771db53859cd436d37a8d6a68a57","repository":"formal_conjectures","source_root":"sha256:6d0afbf6609d6c019d2d8c3cc13bcbe5c8de6d5573e9322ca4e94be2c